Study 1: constant length N*dx = 5 lambda (same beamwidth, AF peak grows with N)
	dx=lambda/2, 10 el: AF peak = 20.00 dB, 3-dB beamwidth = 10.17 deg
	dx=lambda/4, 20 el: AF peak = 26.02 dB, 3-dB beamwidth = 10.14 deg
	dx=lambda/8, 40 el: AF peak = 32.04 dB, 3-dB beamwidth = 10.14 deg
Study 2: constant spacing dx = lambda/2 (longer aperture => narrower beam)
	L=2 lambda,  4 el: AF peak = 12.04 dB, 3-dB beamwidth = 26.26 deg
	L=4 lambda,  8 el: AF peak = 18.06 dB, 3-dB beamwidth = 12.76 deg
	L=8 lambda, 16 el: AF peak = 24.08 dB, 3-dB beamwidth = 6.32 deg
